itools 0.75.1 (2012/12/19)
==========================

itools is a Python library, it groups a number of packages into a single
meta-package for easier development and deployment:

  itools.abnf             itools.ical             itools.srx
  itools.core             itools.log              itools.stl
  itools.csv              itools.loop             itools.tmx
  itools.database         itools.odf              itools.uri
  itools.datatypes        itools.office           itools.web
  itools.fs               itools.pdf              itools.workflow
  itools.gettext          itools.pkg              itools.xliff
  itools.handlers         itools.python           itools.xml
  itools.html             itools.relaxng          itools.xmlfile
  itools.i18n             itools.rss

Dependencies:

- Now pygit2 is not required to install itools from a release (for instance
  with "pip install itools").

  It is only required if you use itools.database or ipkg-build.py or
  ipkg-quality.py

- For those using the PDF-to-text feature (itools.pdf), this release requires
  poppler 0.20 (it won't compile with older versions).

Clean up:

- The itools.git package has been removed: the relevant code has been moved
  where it is used (itools.database and itools.pkg)

- itools.handlers: RWDatabase has been removed

- The ipkg.info.py script has been removed

- The --graph option from the ipkg-quality.py script has been removed

Improvements and fixes:

- The implementation and output of ipkg-build.py has changed a little. Now it
  is able to compile .scss files (requires scss [1])

- Now itools.html understands UmbrUI [2] and jPlayer [3] attributes.
  Contributed by Norman Khine.

- itools.web: fix returned message in Context.come_back
  Contributed by Nicolas Deram


[1] http://sass-lang.com/
[2] https://github.com/n3b/umbrUI
[3] http://www.jplayer.org/


